categories.title: Auto.fun Platform Launch: Technical Issues and Features

content.text:
# Auto.fun Platform Launch Overview

Auto.fun is a token launchpad platform developed by the ElizaOS team that experienced significant technical difficulties during its launch. The platform was repeatedly taken offline due to overwhelming traffic, with users only able to briefly access it before it went down again. The team had to reconfigure servers and temporarily redirected the site to Twitter while addressing these issues.

# Key Technical Issues

- Users reported being charged SOL without tokens being created
- Tokens were created but not properly bonded
- Transaction timeouts during token creation
- Website redirecting to Twitter instead of loading properly
- Swap functionality not working
- Server overload issues shortly after launch
- Users could create duplicate tokens with identical names/tickers
- Wallet connection problems
- Cloudflare configuration issues

The development team acknowledged these issues and established bug reporting channels to track user-reported problems.

# Platform Features

- Token launchpad with AI integration features
- Custom vanity addresses (tokens end with "FUN" in their contract addresses)
- Token-gated chat functionality
- Community content creation tools
- Anti-snipe/bundle features for fairer launches
- Different bonding curve mechanism compared to pump.fun
- Ability to import existing tokens
- Uses Raydium AMM for token creation and trading
- "Fairer than fair" token model allowing project teams to secure up to 50% of tokens pre-listing
- Liquidity NFT mechanics that distribute swap fees to token creators
- LP fees from auto.fun go to ai16z buybacks, which then buys DegenAI

# Token Ecosystem

The platform is connected to two official tokens:

1. **ai16z**: Receives LP fees from auto.fun for buybacks
2. **DegenAI**: Receives buybacks from ai16z

There was some confusion in the community about which tokens were official, with users needing to be cautious about unofficial tokens claiming to be associated with the platform. The community also spent time trying to identify the "first" tokens created on the platform, with several candidates being discussed but no definitive answer provided by the team.

Several documentation improvements were made to the Eliza project. These include adding instrumentation (PR #4261), updating documentation (PR #4281), removing a duplicate Dutch README file (PR #4321), and fixing typos in the changelog (PR #4322). These changes help maintain cleaner documentation and improve the overall quality of the project's supporting materials.

These prices reflect the current market values of these popular cryptocurrencies.

categories.title: Auto.fun Platform Overview and Launch Issues

content.text:
# Auto.fun Platform Overview

Auto.fun is a token launchpad platform developed by the ElizaOS team that allows users to create and trade tokens on Solana. The platform integrates AI features and uses Raydium AMM for token creation and trading. Key features include:

- Custom vanity addresses (tokens end with "FUN" in their contract addresses)
- Token-gated chat functionality
- Community content creation tools
- Anti-snipe/bundle features for fairer launches
- Ability to import existing tokens
- A bonding curve mechanism different from pump.fun
- Liquidity NFTs that allow token deployers to claim fees from burned/graduated LP positions
- A "fairer than fair" token model allowing project teams to secure up to 50% of tokens pre-listing

# Launch Issues and Technical Difficulties

The launch of Auto.fun experienced significant technical difficulties due to overwhelming traffic. Issues included:

- Site repeatedly going up and down, with temporary redirects to their X (Twitter) account
- Server capacity problems requiring reconfiguration
- Transaction timeouts during token creation, with some users losing SOL while contracts were still deployed
- Wallet connection problems
- Cloudflare configuration issues
- Users able to create duplicate tokens with identical names/tickers but different contract addresses
- Tokens created during launch having "low liquidity" flags due to bonding curve configuration issues
- Migration issues with tokens created during brief windows of availability

The development team was actively collecting bug reports and working on fixes throughout the launch period.

# Token Economics and Integration

Auto.fun has a specific token economic model:

- LP fees from Auto.fun go to ai16z buybacks
- The ai16z token then buys DegenAI through an integrated buyback mechanism
- Only ai16z and degenai are official tokens associated with the platform
- The platform does not require tokens for basic functionality to avoid adding friction
- Token creators can update metadata and connect social accounts to their tokens after creation

There are plans for further integration with ElizaOS, including potentially integrating Eliza bots directly into token chats and implementing a community notes system to identify unofficial tokens.

# Development Roadmap

While focusing on stabilizing the Auto.fun platform, the team is also working on other projects including:

- Upgrading SpartanVersus (an automated trading bot) to v2
- Fixing autonomous trading bugs
- Preparing bots for Discord and Telegram integration
- Readying code for open source release
- Developing an AI-to-Solana bridge
- Implementing token-gated chat functionality

The team has successfully reactivated SpartanVersus's Twitter/X account and secured verification (blue checkmark and affiliate badge), with plans for a partnership with Auto.fun for cross-promotion.
